Note: ========================================
Note: HIR to WASM Generator
Note: ========================================
Note: Generates valid WebAssembly Text Format (WAT) from HIR
Note: Part of the Translation translation system
Note: Produces S-expression syntax compliant WAT output
Note: ========================================

Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/backends/wasm/wasm_emitter.runa" as Emitter
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/dictionary.runa" as Dict
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/collections/list.runa" as List
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout

@Reasoning:
Entry point converting a wasm_module HIR dictionary into WebAssembly
Text Format (WAT). Validates the type tag first to avoid producing
nonsense WAT from a wrong-type input.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Null-HIR guard returns 0. Creates a WASM emitter; reads HIR "type"
and bails (destroying the emitter) if absent or not "wasm_module".
Opens the module with "(module" plus optional name, then walks the
top-level sections in canonical order: types, imports, functions,
exports. Closes with ')' and newline. Returns the emitter's output.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints:
Cold path - one call per HIR module. Cost is dominated by function
body translation.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope:
HIR input is trusted. Output ownership follows the emitter's
get_output contract; the emitter is destroyed before return.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "generate_wasm_from_hir" takes hir as Integer returns Integer:
    Note: Main entry point - generate WAT from HIR dictionary

    If hir is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let emitter be proc create_wasm_emitter from Emitter

    Note: Verify this is a WASM module HIR
    Let type_key be proc create_string_literal with "type"
    Let type_value be proc get from Dict with hir, type_key
    If type_value is equal to 0:
        proc destroy_wasm_emitter from Emitter with emitter
        Return 0
    End If

    Let type_str be proc to_cstring from StringCore with type_value
    Let is_wasm be proc string_equals with type_str, "wasm_module"
    If is_wasm is not equal to 1:
        proc destroy_wasm_emitter from Emitter with emitter
        Return 0
    End If

    Note: Start module declaration
    proc emit_string from Emitter with emitter, "(module"

    Note: Generate module name if present
    Let name_key be proc create_string_literal with "name"
    Let name_value be proc get from Dict with hir, name_key
    If name_value is not equal to 0:
        proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32  Note: Space
        Let name_str be proc to_cstring from StringCore with name_value
        proc emit_string from Emitter with emitter, name_str
    End If

    proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 10  Note: Newline

    Note: Generate type declarations
    Let types_key be proc create_string_literal with "types"
    Let types be proc get from Dict with hir, types_key
    If types is not equal to 0:
        proc generate_types with emitter, types
    End If

    Note: Generate imports
    Let imports_key be proc create_string_literal with "imports"
    Let imports be proc get from Dict with hir, imports_key
    If imports is not equal to 0:
        proc generate_imports with emitter, imports
    End If

    Note: Generate functions
    Let functions_key be proc create_string_literal with "functions"
    Let functions be proc get from Dict with hir, functions_key
    If functions is not equal to 0:
        proc generate_functions with emitter, functions
    End If

    Note: Generate exports
    Let exports_key be proc create_string_literal with "exports"
    Let exports be proc get from Dict with hir, exports_key
    If exports is not equal to 0:
        proc generate_exports with emitter, exports
    End If

    Note: Close module
    proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 41  Note: )
    proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 10  Note: Newline

    Let output be proc get_output from Emitter with emitter
    proc destroy_wasm_emitter from Emitter with emitter
    Return output
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emits WASM type declarations - (type $name (func (param T) (result T)))
forms that declare the signature of each function type used by the
module. Required by the WASM binary format for type-checking.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Walks the types list. For each type HIR, emits "  (type" plus the
type name (if any), then " (func". For each entry in "parameters",
emits " (param T)" (T is the type string). For each entry in
"results", emits " (result T)". Closes with "))" and a newline.
@End Implementation

Process called "generate_types" takes emitter as Integer, types as Integer:
    Note: Generate WASM type declarations

    Let type_count be proc size from List with types
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than type_count:
        Let type_hir be proc get from List with types, i

        Note: Indent
        proc emit_string from Emitter with emitter, "  (type"

        Note: Get type name
        Let name_key be proc create_string_literal with "name"
        Let name_value be proc get from Dict with type_hir, name_key
        If name_value is not equal to 0:
            proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32
            Let name_str be proc to_cstring from StringCore with name_value
            proc emit_string from Emitter with emitter, name_str
        End If

        Note: Start function type
        proc emit_string from Emitter with emitter, " (func"

        Note: Generate parameters
        Let params_key be proc create_string_literal with "parameters"
        Let params be proc get from Dict with type_hir, params_key
        If params is not equal to 0:
            Let param_count be proc size from List with params
            Let j be 0
            While j is less than param_count:
                Let param_type be proc get from List with params, j
                proc emit_string from Emitter with emitter, " (param "
                Let param_str be proc to_cstring from StringCore with param_type
                proc emit_string from Emitter with emitter, param_str
                proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 41  Note: )
                Set j to j plus 1
            End While
        End If

        Note: Generate results
        Let results_key be proc create_string_literal with "results"
        Let results be proc get from Dict with type_hir, results_key
        If results is not equal to 0:
            Let result_count be proc size from List with results
            Set j to 0
            While j is less than result_count:
                Let result_type be proc get from List with results, j
                proc emit_string from Emitter with emitter, " (result "
                Let result_str be proc to_cstring from StringCore with result_type
                proc emit_string from Emitter with emitter, result_str
                proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 41  Note: )
                Set j to j plus 1
            End While
        End If

        Note: Close func and type
        proc emit_string from Emitter with emitter, "))"
        proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 10  Note: Newline

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emits WASM import declarations - (import "mod" "name" desc) forms
that bind external symbols (from JavaScript host, other modules) to
module-local identifiers.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Walks the imports list. For each import HIR, emits "  (import ". The
module string is double-quoted (34), then a space, then the name
string is double-quoted, then a space and the descriptor (e.g.,
"(func $name (type $sig))"). Closes with ')' and newline.
@End Implementation

@Security_Scope:
Module and name strings are emitted verbatim between quotes; caller
must ensure they contain no embedded quote characters that would
break the WAT syntax.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "generate_imports" takes emitter as Integer, imports as Integer:
    Note: Generate WASM import declarations

    Let import_count be proc size from List with imports
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than import_count:
        Let import_hir be proc get from List with imports, i

        Note: Indent
        proc emit_string from Emitter with emitter, "  (import "

        Note: Generate module name
        Let module_key be proc create_string_literal with "module"
        Let module_value be proc get from Dict with import_hir, module_key
        If module_value is not equal to 0:
            proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 34  Note: "
            Let module_str be proc to_cstring from StringCore with module_value
            proc emit_string from Emitter with emitter, module_str
            proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 34  Note: "
        End If

        Note: Generate import name
        Let name_key be proc create_string_literal with "name"
        Let name_value be proc get from Dict with import_hir, name_key
        If name_value is not equal to 0:
            proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32  Note: Space
            proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 34  Note: "
            Let name_str be proc to_cstring from StringCore with name_value
            proc emit_string from Emitter with emitter, name_str
            proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 34  Note: "
        End If

        Note: Generate descriptor
        Let desc_key be proc create_string_literal with "descriptor"
        Let desc_value be proc get from Dict with import_hir, desc_key
        If desc_value is not equal to 0:
            proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32  Note: Space
            Let desc_str be proc to_cstring from StringCore with desc_value
            proc emit_string from Emitter with emitter, desc_str
        End If

        Note: Close import
        proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 41  Note: )
        proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 10  Note: Newline

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emits WASM function definitions - the bulk of any WAT module. Each
function has a header (name plus signature), an optional locals list,
and a body of nested-instruction s-expressions.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Walks the functions list. For each function HIR, opens with "  (func"
plus the name (if any) and a newline. Then delegates the signature
to generate_parameters and generate_results, the locals list to
generate_locals, and the body to generate_instructions at indent
level 4. Closes with "  )" and a newline.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints:
Hot path within a single module - one full traversal per function.
Each function body can dominate runtime.
@End Performance_Hints

Process called "generate_functions" takes emitter as Integer, functions as Integer:
    Note: Generate WASM function definitions

    Let func_count be proc size from List with functions
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than func_count:
        Let func_hir be proc get from List with functions, i

        Note: Indent
        proc emit_string from Emitter with emitter, "  (func"

        Note: Generate function name
        Let name_key be proc create_string_literal with "name"
        Let name_value be proc get from Dict with func_hir, name_key
        If name_value is not equal to 0:
            proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32  Note: Space
            Let name_str be proc to_cstring from StringCore with name_value
            proc emit_string from Emitter with emitter, name_str
        End If

        proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 10  Note: Newline

        Note: Generate parameters
        Let params_key be proc create_string_literal with "parameters"
        Let params be proc get from Dict with func_hir, params_key
        If params is not equal to 0:
            proc generate_parameters with emitter, params
        End If

        Note: Generate results
        Let results_key be proc create_string_literal with "results"
        Let results be proc get from Dict with func_hir, results_key
        If results is not equal to 0:
            proc generate_results with emitter, results
        End If

        Note: Generate locals
        Let locals_key be proc create_string_literal with "locals"
        Let locals be proc get from Dict with func_hir, locals_key
        If locals is not equal to 0:
            proc generate_locals with emitter, locals
        End If

        Note: Generate function body
        Let body_key be proc create_string_literal with "body"
        Let body be proc get from Dict with func_hir, body_key
        If body is not equal to 0:
            proc generate_instructions with emitter, body, 4
        End If

        Note: Close function
        proc emit_string from Emitter with emitter, "  )"
        proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 10  Note: Newline

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emits one (param $name T) form per declared function parameter.
Indented 4 spaces to align under the (func ...) header.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Walks the params list. For each param HIR, emits "    (param", then
optionally " $name", then " T" (where T is the param_type), then ')'
and a newline.
@End Implementation

Process called "generate_parameters" takes emitter as Integer, params as Integer:
    Note: Generate function parameters

    Let param_count be proc size from List with params
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than param_count:
        Let param_hir be proc get from List with params, i

        Note: Indent
        proc emit_string from Emitter with emitter, "    (param"

        Note: Generate parameter name
        Let name_key be proc create_string_literal with "name"
        Let name_value be proc get from Dict with param_hir, name_key
        If name_value is not equal to 0:
            proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32  Note: Space
            Let name_str be proc to_cstring from StringCore with name_value
            proc emit_string from Emitter with emitter, name_str
        End If

        Note: Generate parameter type
        Let type_key be proc create_string_literal with "param_type"
        Let type_value be proc get from Dict with param_hir, type_key
        If type_value is not equal to 0:
            proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32  Note: Space
            Let type_str be proc to_cstring from StringCore with type_value
            proc emit_string from Emitter with emitter, type_str
        End If

        proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 41  Note: )
        proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 10  Note: Newline

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emits one (result T) form per declared function result. WASM 1.0
allows at most one result per function but the multi-return-value
proposal lifts this; the loop accommodates both.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Walks the results list. For each result HIR, emits "    (result"
then " T" (where T is the result_type), then ')' and a newline.
@End Implementation

Process called "generate_results" takes emitter as Integer, results as Integer:
    Note: Generate function results

    Let result_count be proc size from List with results
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than result_count:
        Let result_hir be proc get from List with results, i

        Note: Indent
        proc emit_string from Emitter with emitter, "    (result"

        Note: Generate result type
        Let type_key be proc create_string_literal with "result_type"
        Let type_value be proc get from Dict with result_hir, type_key
        If type_value is not equal to 0:
            proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32  Note: Space
            Let type_str be proc to_cstring from StringCore with type_value
            proc emit_string from Emitter with emitter, type_str
        End If

        proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 41  Note: )
        proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 10  Note: Newline

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emits one (local $name T) form per declared local variable in a
function. Locals are addressed by index in WASM bytecode; the WAT
form lets us also give them symbolic names.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Walks the locals list. For each local HIR, emits "    (local",
optionally " $name", then " T" (where T is the local_type), then
')' and a newline.
@End Implementation

Process called "generate_locals" takes emitter as Integer, locals as Integer:
    Note: Generate local variables

    Let local_count be proc size from List with locals
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than local_count:
        Let local_hir be proc get from List with locals, i

        Note: Indent
        proc emit_string from Emitter with emitter, "    (local"

        Note: Generate local name
        Let name_key be proc create_string_literal with "name"
        Let name_value be proc get from Dict with local_hir, name_key
        If name_value is not equal to 0:
            proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32  Note: Space
            Let name_str be proc to_cstring from StringCore with name_value
            proc emit_string from Emitter with emitter, name_str
        End If

        Note: Generate local type
        Let type_key be proc create_string_literal with "local_type"
        Let type_value be proc get from Dict with local_hir, type_key
        If type_value is not equal to 0:
            proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32  Note: Space
            Let type_str be proc to_cstring from StringCore with type_value
            proc emit_string from Emitter with emitter, type_str
        End If

        proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 41  Note: )
        proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 10  Note: Newline

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
End Process

@Reasoning:
Sequencer that emits each instruction in the body in source order at
the supplied indent level. The indent is passed in (not derived
internally) because nested instruction s-expressions must indent
further than their parent.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Walks the instructions list and delegates each entry to
generate_instruction, forwarding indent_level unchanged.
@End Implementation

Process called "generate_instructions" takes emitter as Integer, instructions as Integer, indent_level as Integer:
    Note: Generate instruction list with proper indentation

    Let instr_count be proc size from List with instructions
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than instr_count:
        Let instr_hir be proc get from List with instructions, i
        proc generate_instruction with emitter, instr_hir, indent_level
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
End Process

@Reasoning:
Core recursive emitter for a single WAT instruction. Handles three
shapes: opcode-only ("nop", "drop"), opcode with simple operands
("(i32.const 42)"), and opcode with nested instructions as operands
("(i32.add (local.get $a) (local.get $b))"). Nested instructions
indent further to keep the s-expression structure readable.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Emits the leading indent (a literal space count = indent_level).
Reads the "opcode" string and bails if missing. If "operands" is
non-null, opens with '(' and the opcode, then iterates operands. For
each operand, checks the "type" field: type == "instruction" means
recurse with indent_level + 2 on a new line; otherwise treat as a
simple immediate and emit " value". Closes with ')'. If no operands,
emits the opcode bare. Terminates with a newline.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints:
O(n) in total instruction count including nested children.
Recursion depth bounded by the original HIR's nesting; WAT itself
limits practical nesting in real-world modules.
@End Performance_Hints

Process called "generate_instruction" takes emitter as Integer, instr_hir as Integer, indent_level as Integer:
    Note: Generate a single instruction with proper S-expression nesting

    Note: Emit indentation
    Let indent_count be 0
    While indent_count is less than indent_level:
        proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32  Note: Space
        Set indent_count to indent_count plus 1
    End While

    Note: Get instruction opcode
    Let opcode_key be proc create_string_literal with "opcode"
    Let opcode_value be proc get from Dict with instr_hir, opcode_key
    If opcode_value is equal to 0:
        Return
    End If

    Let opcode_str be proc to_cstring from StringCore with opcode_value

    Note: Check if instruction has operands
    Let operands_key be proc create_string_literal with "operands"
    Let operands be proc get from Dict with instr_hir, operands_key

    If operands is not equal to 0:
        Note: Instruction with operands - use S-expression form
        proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 40  Note: (
        proc emit_string from Emitter with emitter, opcode_str

        Note: Process operands
        Let operand_count be proc size from List with operands
        Let i be 0
        While i is less than operand_count:
            Let operand be proc get from List with operands, i

            Note: Check if operand is nested instruction
            Let type_key be proc create_string_literal with "type"
            Let type_value be proc get from Dict with operand, type_key
            Let type_str be proc to_cstring from StringCore with type_value

            Let is_instruction be proc string_equals with type_str, "instruction"
            If is_instruction is equal to 1:
                Note: Nested instruction - emit on new line with increased indent
                proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 10  Note: Newline
                proc generate_instruction with emitter, operand, indent_level plus 2
            Otherwise:
                Note: Simple operand (immediate value)
                Let value_key be proc create_string_literal with "value"
                Let value_str_obj be proc get from Dict with operand, value_key
                If value_str_obj is not equal to 0:
                    proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32  Note: Space
                    Let value_str be proc to_cstring from StringCore with value_str_obj
                    proc emit_string from Emitter with emitter, value_str
                End If
            End If

            Set i to i plus 1
        End While

        proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 41  Note: )
    Otherwise:
        Note: Simple instruction without operands
        proc emit_string from Emitter with emitter, opcode_str
    End If

    proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 10  Note: Newline
End Process

@Reasoning:
Emits WASM export declarations - (export "name" $internal) forms
exposing internal symbols to the host environment under (possibly
different) external names.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Walks the exports list. For each export HIR, emits "  (export ", a
double-quoted name string, a space, then the internal reference
verbatim (e.g., "(func $foo)"). Closes with ')' and a newline.
@End Implementation

@Security_Scope:
Export name is double-quoted; caller must ensure it contains no
embedded quote characters.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "generate_exports" takes emitter as Integer, exports as Integer:
    Note: Generate WASM export declarations

    Let export_count be proc size from List with exports
    Let i be 0

    While i is less than export_count:
        Let export_hir be proc get from List with exports, i

        Note: Indent
        proc emit_string from Emitter with emitter, "  (export "

        Note: Generate export name
        Let name_key be proc create_string_literal with "name"
        Let name_value be proc get from Dict with export_hir, name_key
        If name_value is not equal to 0:
            proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 34  Note: "
            Let name_str be proc to_cstring from StringCore with name_value
            proc emit_string from Emitter with emitter, name_str
            proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 34  Note: "
        End If

        Note: Generate internal reference
        Let internal_key be proc create_string_literal with "internal_name"
        Let internal_value be proc get from Dict with export_hir, internal_key
        If internal_value is not equal to 0:
            proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 32  Note: Space
            Let internal_str be proc to_cstring from StringCore with internal_value
            proc emit_string from Emitter with emitter, internal_str
        End If

        Note: Close export
        proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 41  Note: )
        proc emit_char from Emitter with emitter, 10  Note: Newline

        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
End Process

@Reasoning:
Local null-terminated string compare, inlined to keep the dispatcher
hot path dependency-light.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation:
Byte-by-byte walk; returns 0 on first mismatch, 1 when both bytes
hit NUL simultaneously. Sentinel-free infinite-loop form.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints:
O(n) in shorter string length. No allocation.
@End Performance_Hints

Process called "string_equals" takes str1 as String, str2 as String returns Integer:
    Note: Compare two null-terminated strings for equality

    Let i be 0
    While 1 is equal to 1:
        Let c1 be proc memory_get_byte from Layout with str1, i
        Let c2 be proc memory_get_byte from Layout with str2, i
        If c1 is not equal to c2:
            Return 0
        End If
        If c1 is equal to 0:
            Return 1
        End If
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Local alias for StringCore.create_string_from_literal; keeps call
sites concise.
@End Reasoning

Process called "create_string_literal" takes value as String returns Integer:
    Return proc create_string_from_literal from StringCore with value
End Process
